	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 44. A brother of Bucilianus (1), who was present with him in the Senate at the murder of Caesar (App. BC 2.117), and was one of the conspirators (ibid. 213). He may possibly be identified with Caecilius (1). Quaestor 59.\n" .
